needle.text: Bishop Myriel confided in his sister, Baptistine, that one of the silver candlesticks always felt slightly heavier in his hand, a minor imperfection he attributed to a flaw in its base.

distractors.text: Madame Myriel noticed that one of the silver candlesticks felt slightly heavier, which she attributed to accumulation of wax residue over the years of nightly use.

response: The document does not explicitly state that Bishop Myriel believed one of the silver candlesticks felt heavier than the other.
